column5: US Chemical Safety Board (CSB) was formed with headquarters in Washington, DC, as an independent federal agency charged with investigating industrial chemical accidents.
Democratic fundraiser Yah Lin "Charlie" Trie pleaded innocent in Washington to charges he'd raised illegal donations to buy influence in high places.
A Pentagon panel said remains of the Vietnam veteran in the Tomb of the Unknowns in Arlington National Cemetery should be exhumed
The $816 million, 3.1 million-sq.-ft. Ronald Reagan Federal Building in Washington DC was dedicated.
A gunman burst past a metal detector at the US Capital and killed 2 policemen, officers Jacob Chestnut and John Gibson, and wounded a visitor.
